## 3. Wiki layout

```
wiki/
  index.md            Page catalog. `okf_version` frontmatter + hand-written prose;
                      the per-category listing is GENERATED (scripts/build_index.py).
  log.md              Timeline of ingests/queries/lints — newest first, OKF date groups.
  overview.md         Top-level synthesis: what the product is.
  entities/           The nouns.        e.g. <entity>.md
  concepts/           The ideas.        e.g. authentication.md
  processes/          The workflows.    e.g. login.md
  rules/              The constraints.  e.g. authentication-rules.md
  terminology/        glossary.md + acronym definitions.
```

- **Page slug = the concept, kebab-case.** `sample-set.md`, never `proj-37.md`.
- One concept per page. If a page grows to cover two concepts, split it.
- Connect pages with Obsidian `[[wikilinks]]` so the graph view stays useful.
  A `[[link]]` to a page that doesn't exist yet is fine — it's a TODO marker.

Imports live under `raw/imports/` — Jira at `raw/imports/jira/<KEY>.md`; converted docs at
`raw/imports/<hash8>/<name>.md` (or in place under `raw/`). Code and plain-text sources have
**no import** (synthesize reads them directly). Imports are the *extract* output; the wiki is
the *synthesize* output. Their body format is the extractor's call (§5); only a minimal
routing header is fixed.

