## 6. index.md and log.md

**`index.md`** — content catalog. Read it first on every query. It has three parts:
an `okf_version: "0.1"` frontmatter block (the only frontmatter OKF permits in an
index), hand-written prose (intro, source/naming notes — yours to maintain), and the
per-category page listing inside `<!-- catalog:begin -->` … `<!-- catalog:end -->`
markers. The marker region is **generated** from page `description:` frontmatter by
`scripts/build_index.py --write` — never hand-edit it; edit the page's `description:`
and regenerate. Lint fails on any drift between the two.

**`log.md`** — greppable event timeline in OKF form: `## YYYY-MM-DD` date headings,
one `- <op> | <payload>` bullet per event, **newest first** throughout. To record an
event, *prepend* the bullet directly under today's heading (create `## <today>` above
the first date heading if it doesn't exist yet). Recent events: `head -30 wiki/log.md`.
`synth` is the event that records wiki changes (with the underlying sources); extract
is tracked by the queues/imports, not the log:

```
## 2026-06-10
- lint --full | manual | scope: 59 pages, 5 shards | CLEAN

## 2026-06-09
- lint | auto   | scope: 14 pages since last lint + neighbors | FIXED 1 broken link
- query  | "how does the product authenticate?" | pages read: authentication, login
- synth  | PROJ-37 (story, 2017-11) | pages: login, authentication, glossary
```

`lint | auto` is a synth-gate delta; `lint | manual` a hand-run delta; `lint --full` a full
audit. All three are the lint watermark — the topmost `- lint` bullet, since newest is
first (the `auto|manual` field is traceability only).

**State is which queue a line is in.** An identity (Jira KEY or absolute path) lives in
exactly one of `<config_dir>/state/<source>.{extract,synth}`, or neither (done) — its location is
its state; an import at `raw/imports/jira/<KEY>.md` (or a converted `.md` under `raw/imports/`) means an awkward source is extracted.
`<config_dir>/state/jira-cursor.json` holds **only** the per-project Jira source-scan cursor
(machine-local runtime state, alongside the queues); the git source scan is stateless (the repo's own HEAD is
the watermark). Before working, check state (`queues.py status`) so you never re-process a
source.

